-- Stocks in Switzerland Advance Before U.S. Durable-Goods Report
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2013-09-25T09:31:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-25/stocks-in-switzerland-advance-before-u-s-durable-goods-report.html
Swiss stocks advanced, following a
two-day decline, as investors awaited reports on U.S. durable-goods orders and new house sales.  Swissquote Group Holding SA surged 7.9 percent after
agreeing to buy MIG Bank for an undisclosed price. Clariant AG
lost 1.4 percent after UBS AG removed the maker of specialty
chemicals from the list of its most preferred shares.  The Swiss Market Index gained 0.3 percent to 8,068.64 at
11:28 a.m. in Zurich. The equity benchmark has climbed 4.2
percent this month, extending its gain this quarter to 5
percent. The Swiss Performance Index rose 0.2 percent today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
